<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="530" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,404,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="530">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name of 
<taxonomicName box="[580,698,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[580,698,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="530">M. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers sharply bicolored body in which the thorax is orange below and dark above, and in which the dark upper thorax contrasts with the reddish abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="530" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,476,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="530">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,568,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[344,568,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="530">Mesoconius bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusual amongst congeners for its occurrence at relatively low altitudes, ranging down to 
<specimenCount box="[341,420,512,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="530" type="generic">
<quantity box="[341,415,512,536]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="530" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
